{"serial": "21070", "department_serial": 20, "code": "MA5502", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Mathematical Foundations of Quantum Information", "ch": "量子資訊的數學基礎"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "歡迎大三、大四選課"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Lee, Yen-Chi"], "ch": ["李彥奇"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["5", "6"]}, "loc": {"building": "M", "room": "328"}}, {"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["5"]}, "loc": {"building": "M", "room": "328"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "數學系", "en": "Department of Mathematics"}, "system": {"ch": "碩士班", "en": "Master Programs"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 28, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "歡迎大三、大四選課", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "這門課程旨在為學生提供對量子資訊理論之數學基礎的嚴謹理解。課程將涵蓋的主題如希爾伯特空間、量子態、線性算子、量子通道，以及它們在量子計算和量子通信中的應用。此課程旨在使學生掌握分析量子系統所需的基本工具，並為未來進一步學習或研究量子資訊科學做好準備。", "en": "The course “Mathematical Foundations of Quantum Information“ aims to provide students with a rigorous understanding of the mathematical concepts underpinning quantum information theory. It will cover essential topics such as Hilbert spaces, quantum states, linear operators, and quantum channels, along with their applications in quantum computation and communication. The course is designed to equip students with the basic tools needed to analyze quantum systems and prepare them for advanced study or research in quantum information science."}, "outline": {"ch": "本課程將涵蓋以下主題：\n一、量子資訊的數學框架與符號約定（封閉量子系統與開放量子系統）\n二、量子計算的基礎\n三、量子資訊論（量子通道、距離測度、熵與資訊量度）", "en": "We will cover the following topics:\n1. The mathematical framework of quantum information (including noiseless and noisy quantum theories)\n2. Fundamentals of quantum computation\n3. Quantum information theory (covering quantum channels, distance measures, entropy and information measure)"}, "textbook": {"ch": "Main references:\n1. Michael Nielsen and Issac Chuang. “Quantum Computation and Quantum Information (10th Anniversary Edition),“ Cambridge University Press, 2010.\n2. Mark M. Wilde. “Quantum Information Theory (2nd Edition),“ Cambridge University Press, 2017.\n3. Lecture notes by Christoph Dittel: http://arxiv.org/abs/2311.12442\n4. Lecture notes by Felix Leditzky: “Quantum Channels - Theory and Applications.“\n5. John Watrous, “The Theory of Quantum Information,“ Cambridge University Press, 2018.\n\n註：無合適中文書", "en": "Main references:\n1. Michael Nielsen and Issac Chuang. “Quantum Computation and Quantum Information (10th Anniversary Edition),“ Cambridge University Press, 2010.\n2. Mark M. Wilde. “Quantum Information Theory (2nd Edition),“ Cambridge University Press, 2017.\n3. Lecture notes by Christoph Dittel: http://arxiv.org/abs/2311.12442\n4. Lecture notes by Felix Leditzky: “Quantum Channels - Theory and Applications.“\n5. John Watrous, “The Theory of Quantum Information,“ Cambridge University Press, 2018."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "30%", "en": "30%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "作業或報告40％、期中考30％、期末考30％", "en": "Homework or Report 40％, Midterm 30％, Final Exam 30％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "四34 (請先預約)", "en": "Thu 10:00-11:50 (by appointment)"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "17+1", "en": "17+1"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "第18週為自主學習", "en": "Week 18 is for self-directed learning."}, "domain": {"ch": "理論數學", "en": "理論數學"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知識", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習"]}, {"competencies": "學術研究", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習"]}, {"competencies": "獨立思考", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習"]}, {"competencies": "國際視野", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "終身學習", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["出席/課堂表現"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Professional knowledge", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments"]}, {"competencies": "Academic research", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Ex